{"TopicId":136345,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Suggestion - Window-only transparency","CreatedByName":"TaintedLion","CreatedById":137942,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-07T23:55:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"TaintedLion","CreatedById":137942,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-07T23:55:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the IVA cutaway feature coming in 1.1, what I thought would be a great idea would be to make only the windows transparent, so we can see inside without the entire cutaway, just the windows, like this;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/0hR6J/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCredit to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/48847-rbray89/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002248847\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/48847-rbray89/\u0022\u003E@rbray89\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for doing some fantastic work with EVE to make these windows work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust my two cents, I feel this is a feature that is being missed out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-09T10:22:47Z\u0022 title=\u002204/09/2016 10:22  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by TaintedLion\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RA3236","CreatedById":150734,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T02:15:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually not a bad idea \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T02:36:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot just \u0022not a bad idea.\u0022 It should be a setting in a config or menu option somewhere to be the default.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"monstah","CreatedById":95210,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T12:04:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe frost on the cupola glass is\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eespecially\u003C/em\u003E nice. Indeed, we need this \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T12:08:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would be so cool indeed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Grumman","CreatedById":76014,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T12:19:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222501543\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022136345\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221460082965\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot just \u0022not a bad idea.\u0022 It should be a setting in a config or menu option somewhere to be the default.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr just make it a three setting toggle instead of two: opaque, window only, wall\u0026amp;window.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Whirligig Girl","CreatedById":36077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T12:21:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222502150\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022136345\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221460117994\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Grumman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Grumman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr just make it a three setting toggle instead of two: opaque, window only, wall\u0026amp;window.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd make the toggle persistent instead of going away when you go IVA or to the map view.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T12:30:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be nice to have actual transparent cockpits; but with that said, I do love the new cutaway views, too. The only concern I have is what would happen to the framerate/GPU requirements if such a feature was added? Not that I am saying it is a bad idea, but for those of us who are already operating on the edge of KSP playing like a Microsoft Power Point presentation, this might not be a good thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T13:23:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, it is possible to use the feature in that exact way when modding. \u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106805-nli2work/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022106805\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106805-nli2work/\u0022\u003E@nli2work\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0has a great thread about it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/135597-iva-overlay-setup/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do think it would be a nice toggle, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nli2work","CreatedById":106805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T14:18:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can achieve window transparency with Overlay feature in stock already. It\u0027s up to how the modeler set it up to get different visual affects. It\u0027s a matter of art direction, not a lack of game feature.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI believe RPM will have an updated version of TransparentPod module that has some extra features. Again, the decision is up to individual modeler.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPersonally I think it\u0027s a nice, but not necessary\u00A0feature. Aside from taking a few screen shots, and making in game videos, it doesn\u0027t have much use. It doesn\u0027t add much in the way of game play.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-08T14:23:11Z\u0022 title=\u002204/08/2016 02:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by nli2work\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T14:45:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222502324\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022136345\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221460125083\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106805\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nli2work\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, nli2work said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit doesn\u0027t have much use.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it\u0027s so useful in positioning your IVA, though. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T15:09:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222502324\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022136345\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221460125083\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106805\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nli2work\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, nli2work said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can achieve window transparency with Overlay feature in stock already. It\u0027s up to how the modeler set it up to get different visual affects. It\u0027s a matter of art direction, not a lack of game feature.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI believe RPM will have an updated version of TransparentPod module that has some extra features. Again, the decision is up to individual modeler.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPersonally I think it\u0027s a nice, but not necessary\u00A0feature. Aside from taking a few screen shots, and making in game videos, it doesn\u0027t have much use. It doesn\u0027t add much in the way of game play.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re right. It doesn\u0027t have much of a practical use. However, neither do many of the accessories we get on cars, but they are nice to have features. I see this transparent canopy thing in the same light... it\u0027s nice to have although not completely necessary...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222502365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022136345\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221460126728\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022140061\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CliftonM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, CliftonM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it\u0027s so useful in positioning your IVA, though. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, it is... But again, it is not a necessity but just a really neat feature. I actually like the cut-away view because it reminds me of the old 1950s and 1960s \u003Cem\u003EPopular Mechanics\u003C/em\u003E magazines my grandparents kept around.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbonautInTraining","CreatedById":145373,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T19:30:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222502166\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022136345\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221460118640\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only concern I have is what would happen to the framerate/GPU requirements if such a feature was added?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe interiors are already loaded to show the Kerbal\u0027s portraits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalBuzzsaw","CreatedById":158329,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T19:46:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYESYESYES\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-08T21:23:51Z\u0022 title=\u002204/08/2016 09:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Red Iron Crown\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EDon\u0026#039;t do that.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Windspren","CreatedById":134441,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T20:32:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell. That might be a \u003Cem\u003Ebit \u003C/em\u003Etoo spammy for my tastes.^^\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalBuzzsaw","CreatedById":158329,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T20:43:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk so maybe I fell asleep on the CTRL V\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RocketSquid","CreatedById":152665,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T21:31:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDeploying support...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*BOOOOM*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSupport deployed. This is a good idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T22:45:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T23:16:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve always supported this idea.\u00A0 Now with 1.1 it\u0027s like it is right outside our grasp lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}